'''Docking Bay 86''' was a starship [[Hangar/Legends|hangar]] area located in the port city of [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].<ref name="GG8" />

==History==
In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]], [[Spurch Goa|Spurch "Warhog" Goa]] docked his [[Cruiser/Legends|cruiser]], the ''[[Nova Viper]]'', here while searching for work from the planet's criminal kingpin, [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]].<ref name="ahf">{{StoryCite|story=A Hunter's Fate: Greedo's Tale|book=Tales from the Mos Eisley Cantina}}</ref>

Later, in [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]], the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]] used this [[Hangar/Legends|docking bay]] for her starship, the ''[[Pok's Demise]]'' on a layover on Tatooine. She was forced to flee the bay in her ship when chased by bounty hunters.<ref name="sot">{{GalaxyCite|10|Sandbound on Tatooine}}</ref>

It was also the place where the ''[[Pulsar Skate]]'' was berthed while [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]], [[Mirax Terrik Horn|Mirax Terrik]] and [[Gavin Darklighter]] visited [[Huff Darklighter]] to buy arms and armor for [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]], during the [[Bacta War]]. At that time, Docking Bay 86 was owned by a relative of Gavin's.<ref name="tbw">''[[X-Wing: The Bacta War]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Docking_Bay_86_on_map.jpg|250px|thumb|Docking Bay 86 on a map of Mos Eisley]]
''[[Galaxy Guide 7: Mos Eisley]]'' lists Docking Bay 86 as being one of the docking bays owned by [[Chachi De Maal/Legends|Chachi]] and [[Ohwun De Maal/Legends|Ohwun De Maal]]. Later in the same book it lists the docking bay as being the property of absentee owner [[Trepler Darklighter]].<ref name="GG8" />

